Here is a C++ function to convert markdown to HTML:

```cpp
#include <string>

std::string markdownToHTML(const std::string& markdown) {
  std::string html;

  // Logic to parse markdown and generate HTML

  // Replace markdown headers with HTML tags
  html = std::regex_replace(markdown, std::regex("^#+(.*)$"), "<h$1>$2</h$1>"); 

  // Replace markdown bold with HTML bold
  html = std::regex_replace(html, std::regex("\\*\\*(.*?)\\*\\*"), "<b>$1</b>");

  // Replace markdown italics with HTML italics
  html = std::regex_replace(html, std::regex("_(.*?)_"), "<i>$1</i>");

  // Replace markdown links with HTML links
  html = std::regex_replace(html, std::regex("\\[([^\\]]*)\\]\\(([^\\)]*)\\)"), "<a href=\"$2\">$1</a>");

  // Other markdown to HTML logic

  return html;
}
```

This implements basic markdown to HTML conversion by using std::regex_replace to match markdown syntax and replace it with corresponding HTML tags. Additional logic would be needed to fully support all markdown features.

